User Story: As a developer, I want to create the FileLoad entity, so that I can represent file load information in the database.

Acceptance Criteria:

The model module contains the FileLoad entity class.

The FileLoad entity includes fields for

id (primary key, auto-generated)

filename

loadDate (timestamp)

status

recordCount

errors (string for error messages, or a collection of errors)

The FileLoad entity is annotated with @Entity and JPA annotations.

The FileLoad entity defines the mapping to the file load staging table in the database.

2. User Story: As a developer, I want to create DTOs for API requests and responses, so that I can control the data format.

Acceptance Criteria:

The model module contains DTO classes for

FileLoadRequestDTO (for creating/updating file loads)

FileLoadResponseDTO (for returning file load information)

Search Criteria DTO (for defining search parameters)

DTOs include only the necessary fields for each operation

DTOs are annotated with validation annotations (e.g. @NotNull Size Pattem) where appropriate.
